==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nazarite
<hw>Naz"a*rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A Jew bound
by a vow to leave the hair uncut, to abstain from wine and strong drink,
and to practice extraordinary purity of life and devotion, the
obligation being for life, or for a certain time. The word is also used
adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nazariteship</ent>⟦br⟧
